# Logistic regression

colnames(data1)
##  [1] "Date"                       "TempHighF"                 
##  [3] "TempAvgF"                   "TempLowF"                  
##  [5] "DewPointHighF"              "DewPointAvgF"              
##  [7] "DewPointLowF"               "HumidityHighPercent"       
##  [9] "HumidityAvgPercent"         "HumidityLowPercent"        
## [11] "SeaLevelPressureHighInches" "SeaLevelPressureAvgInches" 
## [13] "SeaLevelPressureLowInches"  "VisibilityHighMiles"       
## [15] "VisibilityAvgMiles"         "VisibilityLowMiles"        
## [17] "WindHighMPH"                "WindAvgMPH"

## [21] "Rain"                       "RainP"
model <- glm(Rain ~ TempHighF+TempAvgF+TempLowF+DewPointHighF+DewPointAvgF+DewPointLowF+HumidityHighPercent+HumidityAvgPercent+HumidityLowPercent+SeaLevelPressureHighInches+SeaLevelPressureAvgInches+VisibilityLowMiles+VisibilityHighMiles+VisibilityAvgMiles+WindGustMPH+WindHighMPH+WindAvgMPH, data = train.df, family = binomial)
